01:18:44,762 --> 01:18:45,763
No, daddy.

775
01:18:47,640 --> 01:18:48,937
Not this time.

776
01:19:10,871 --> 01:19:13,795
Psst. Hey. Hey.

777
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:15,922
Can you hear me?

778
01:19:18,254 --> 01:19:21,133
Next time he asks you where his
daughter's head is, answer him.

779
01:19:21,257 --> 01:19:24,761
- But I don't know.
- That's not the point!

780
01:19:24,885 --> 01:19:26,387
We're dealing with a nutcase.

781
01:19:26,512 --> 01:19:28,685
Just name a place,
buy us some time.

782
01:19:32,101 --> 01:19:33,227
Got it?

783
01:19:38,023 --> 01:19:39,900
Just don't tell him right away.

784
01:19:40,025 --> 01:19:41,322
Take some pain first.

785
01:19:42,403 --> 01:19:43,871
Take some pain first?

786
01:19:46,240 --> 01:19:49,369
Yes, for a bit, so that he
doesn't get suspicious.

787
01:19:49,493 --> 01:19:51,621
And then tell him.
Understood?

788
01:19:52,830 --> 01:19:53,877
Understood?!

789
01:19:54,957 --> 01:19:56,049
Mm-hmm.

790
01:20:01,630 --> 01:20:03,257
So what's the plan?

791
01:20:04,758 --> 01:20:07,807
- What?
- I want to help.

792
01:20:07,928 --> 01:20:11,523
- What do you mean "help?"
- I gather he's not talking.

793
01:20:11,640 --> 01:20:13,483
Come on, dad.

794
01:20:13,600 --> 01:20:15,352
Go home to mom.

795
01:20:15,477 --> 01:20:18,230
I'm not leaving until he talks.

796
01:20:20,774 --> 01:20:22,742
Then tell mom
you're sleeping over.

797
01:20:22,860 --> 01:20:24,612
The bastard won't be
talking any time soon.

798
01:20:28,866 --> 01:20:31,289
Have you done
the fire test yet?

799
01:20:32,369 --> 01:20:34,747
"Fire test?"

800
01:20:34,872 --> 01:20:38,627
They don't teach you anything
in the army these days, huh?

801
01:20:38,751 --> 01:20:42,096
If there's one thing I learned
while serving in the army...

802
01:20:42,212 --> 01:20:44,465
is that, much like animals...

803
01:20:44,590 --> 01:20:47,514
what scares people
the most is fire.

804
01:20:48,761 --> 01:20:50,388
Fire, you say.

805
01:20:52,639 --> 01:20:54,892
I need a blowtorch.

806
01:21:56,286 --> 01:21:59,586
So you're the son of a bitch
who killed my granddaughter.

807
01:22:04,837 --> 01:22:08,307
What kind of monster
would do such a thing?

808
01:22:09,466 --> 01:22:11,218
What are you doing?

809
01:22:11,343 --> 01:22:15,564
Patience. You'll know
everything soon enough.

810
01:22:15,681 --> 01:22:19,151
Gidin'ka, will I have
to wait much longer?

811
01:22:20,477 --> 01:22:22,275
Sorry, it took me
a while to find it.

812
01:22:25,023 --> 01:22:28,573
- Dad, what are you doing?
- Defrosting the meat.

813
01:22:28,694 --> 01:22:31,538
That's great,
but that's the wrong meat.

814
01:22:34,241 --> 01:22:36,164
That's the cop.

815
01:22:36,285 --> 01:22:38,458
- That's the pedophile.
- Ah.

816
01:22:50,507 --> 01:22:53,056
How could I confuse the two?

817
01:22:53,177 --> 01:22:56,397
It never used to
happen to me. it's age.

818
01:22:56,513 --> 01:22:59,016
It does terrible things
to the mind.

819
01:22:59,141 --> 01:23:01,439
Your mind is fine, dad.

820
01:23:01,560 --> 01:23:03,528
I can understand
your confusion.

821
01:23:03,645 --> 01:23:06,990
- You're just saying that.
- No, I can really understand.

822
01:23:07,107 --> 01:23:09,405
He looks more like
a pedophile than him.

823
01:23:12,779 --> 01:23:15,828
This one looks like
he couldn't hurt a fly.

824
01:23:15,949 --> 01:23:18,077
That's why he hurts
little girls.

825
01:23:34,218 --> 01:23:36,266
What are you doing?

826
01:23:36,386 --> 01:23:38,889
I hear you're not
talking to my son.

827
01:23:40,098 --> 01:23:42,692
I told him I didn't do it.

828
01:23:44,061 --> 01:23:45,734
Now I'm telling you the same.

829
01:23:47,231 --> 01:23:50,531
Could you talk to him?
Calm him down?

830
01:23:50,651 --> 01:23:53,575
You have my word
that I'll talk to him...

831
01:23:53,695 --> 01:23:56,665
but first I want you
to answer one question.

832
01:23:57,783 --> 01:23:59,660
Look at me.

833
01:23:59,785 --> 01:24:02,664
If I knew something, don't you
think I'd tell him by now?

834
01:24:02,788 --> 01:24:04,005
Maybe.

835
01:24:05,165 --> 01:24:07,634
But just to be
on the safe side...

836
01:24:09,002 --> 01:24:12,506
I'll ask one more time.

837
01:24:14,258 --> 01:24:15,555
Gidin'ka...

838
01:24:17,803 --> 01:24:19,430
the blowtorch.

839
01:24:25,561 --> 01:24:28,405
Are you going
to tell me where you...

840
01:24:28,480 --> 01:24:30,482
buried my granddaughter's head?

841
01:24:36,947 --> 01:24:38,540
I really don't know.

842
01:25:01,546 --> 01:25:02,893
No!

843
01:25:27,122 --> 01:25:29,500
You smell that, Gidin'ka?

844
01:25:29,625 --> 01:25:32,299
It smells like a barbeque.

845
01:25:32,419 --> 01:25:35,798
You have no idea how much
I've missed that smell.

846
01:25:35,922 --> 01:25:38,596
His mom turned
me into a vegetarian...

847
01:25:38,717 --> 01:25:40,435
because cf my high cholesterol.

848
01:25:43,013 --> 01:25:46,062
Oh, I could go on all night!

849
01:25:47,934 --> 01:25:49,732
Gidin'ka...

850
01:25:49,853 --> 01:25:52,948
I remember you loved
hot clogs as a kid.

851
01:25:53,065 --> 01:25:56,786
- Do you still like hot dogs?
- Who doesn't?

852
01:26:06,912 --> 01:26:10,587
No! No,
I'll talk! I'll talk!

853
01:26:14,544 --> 01:26:16,592
I told you, Gidin'ka.

854
01:26:16,713 --> 01:26:19,637
When it comes to the balls,
everyone talks.

855
01:26:33,814 --> 01:26:35,361
Talk.

856
01:26:37,275 --> 01:26:39,152
The girl...

857
01:26:39,277 --> 01:26:41,905
She's buried
in a derelict greenhouse...

858
01:26:43,198 --> 01:26:45,121
five hundred yards behind
the school...

859
01:26:46,535 --> 01:26:48,162
where the new wing
is being built...

860
01:26:49,454 --> 01:26:51,127
in the southern corner...

861
01:26:52,958 --> 01:26:55,086
right underneath a fan.

862
01:26:59,339 --> 01:27:01,091
See?

863
01:27:02,843 --> 01:27:04,720
Where there's a will,
there's a way.

864
01:27:17,649 --> 01:27:20,573
I think I earned you today.

865
01:27:22,279 --> 01:27:25,829
Gidin'ka, don't tell
your mother about this, okay?

866
01:27:25,949 --> 01:27:28,202
It'll be our little secret.

867
01:27:28,326 --> 01:27:30,203
You're full
of surprises today, huh?

868
01:27:31,588 --> 01:27:33,040
Dad...

869
01:27:33,165 --> 01:27:35,588
I need you to watch over
these two until I get back.

870
01:27:37,419 --> 01:27:39,421
You can trust me.

871
01:28:18,585 --> 01:28:19,928
My wife.

872
01:28:21,588 --> 01:28:24,057
- Hello, Malka!
- Hello.

873
01:28:24,174 --> 01:28:26,518
Can you hear me?

874
01:28:26,635 --> 01:28:30,230
- Do you know what time it is?
- I do, I do.

875
01:28:30,347 --> 01:28:32,349
Why didn't you call
to say you'd be late?

876
01:28:32,474 --> 01:28:34,476
I was busy with our son.

877
01:28:34,601 --> 01:28:36,979
How's he feeling?
Did you have soup?

878
01:28:37,103 --> 01:28:39,231
We did.
It was delicious.

879
01:28:39,356 --> 01:28:41,700
So what are youndoing there?
Are you smoking again?

880
01:28:41,817 --> 01:28:44,036
Of course not.

881
01:28:44,152 --> 01:28:47,156
Did you take your pill?

882
01:28:47,280 --> 01:28:49,374
- I forgot.
- Of course you did!

883
01:28:49,491 --> 01:28:51,539
If I'm not there
to remind you, who will?

884
01:28:51,660 --> 01:28:55,961
Take it now and eat
something solid beforehand.

885
01:28:56,081 --> 01:28:57,958
Okay, Malka. Okay.

886
01:28:58,083 --> 01:29:00,552
Otherwise you'll
have gas all night.

887
01:29:02,587 --> 01:29:06,012
Well, I'm going to sleep.
Be quiet when you come to bed.

888
01:29:06,132 --> 01:29:09,011
I promise, Malka.
Good night.

889
01:29:09,135 --> 01:29:11,479
I'll be as quiet as a cricket.

890
01:29:26,319 --> 01:29:28,321
Something solid.

891
01:29:28,446 --> 01:29:31,290
Where will
I find something solid?

892
01:29:34,077 --> 01:29:36,671
This place is like
a student dorm.

893
01:29:36,788 --> 01:29:38,631
Bingo!

894
01:29:38,748 --> 01:29:40,716
Cake with frosting!

895
01:29:46,715 --> 01:29:47,887
Not bad.

896
01:29:49,342 --> 01:29:50,559
Not bad at all.

897
01:30:08,028 --> 01:30:11,282
Hope you're not mad at me
for not offering you some.

898
01:30:11,406 --> 01:30:15,252
I have to eat some solid food
before taking my pill.

899
01:33:08,917 --> 01:33:11,466
Never cuff a cop.

900
01:33:24,099 --> 01:33:26,022
Come on, untie me.

901
01:33:26,142 --> 01:33:28,236
No, in your condition
you'd only slow me down.

902
01:33:28,353 --> 01:33:31,732
But I did what you asked me to do,
I bought us some time. Untie me.

903
01:33:31,856 --> 01:33:34,655
Listen, I'm going to get help.
I'll be right back.

904
01:33:34,776 --> 01:33:36,653
Don't leave me
with this lunatic!

905
01:33:36,778 --> 01:33:39,547
He won't find anything there.
He'll come back and slaughter me!

906
01:35:00,820 --> 01:35:02,493
You have to help me.

907
01:35:11,664 --> 01:35:13,166
Why did you stop?

908
01:35:15,752 --> 01:35:17,550
I have to know.

909
01:35:18,838 --> 01:35:19,839
To know what?

910
01:35:24,510 --> 01:35:27,935
- Look me in the eye.
- You can't be serious.

911
01:35:28,056 --> 01:35:30,605
He'll be back any minute now.

912
01:35:30,725 --> 01:35:33,899
- Did you do it?
- I didn't do a thing.

913
01:35:34,020 --> 01:35:35,693
Untie me!

914
01:35:43,404 --> 01:35:45,827
If you don't release me now,
you're making a big mistake.

915
01:35:50,161 --> 01:35:52,289
You'll regret it
for the rest of your life.

916
01:37:18,916 --> 01:37:20,008
Good evening.

917
01:37:22,253 --> 01:37:25,348
Why do you Jews always think
that we all want to kill you?

918
01:37:25,465 --> 01:37:27,513
No, not at all, but...

919
01:37:27,633 --> 01:37:29,556
you know how it is.

920
01:37:29,677 --> 01:37:31,395
Yes, unfortunately I do.

921
01:37:31,512 --> 01:37:34,766
Yeah. Say...

922
01:37:34,891 --> 01:37:37,189
you wouldn't have
a cellphone, would you?

923
01:37:37,310 --> 01:37:39,187
Why not?
Because we're primitive?

924
01:37:39,312 --> 01:37:42,532
- No, why do you say that?
- Isn't that what you think?

925
01:37:42,648 --> 01:37:44,696
Nut at all. If anybody's
primitive here, it's us.

926
01:37:44,817 --> 01:37:47,536
You people have the right idea.

927
01:37:52,992 --> 01:37:54,790
- May I?
- Yes, sure.

928
01:37:56,871 --> 01:37:58,464
Thank you.

929
01:37:58,581 --> 01:38:00,458
An iPhone, huh?

930
01:38:00,583 --> 01:38:03,132
- 4S.
- Nice. Thanks.

931
01:38:03,252 --> 01:38:04,879
You're a life saver.

932
01:38:08,508 --> 01:38:10,431
- Tsvika's office.
- Who is it? Rona?

933
01:38:10,551 --> 01:38:13,020
- Efrat.
- It's Micki. Put Tsvika on the phone.

934
01:38:13,137 --> 01:38:14,810
He's been looking
everywhere for you.

935
01:38:14,931 --> 01:38:16,774
That's why I called.
Put him on.

936
01:38:25,983 --> 01:38:27,485
Do you know how long
I've been looking for you?

937
01:38:27,610 --> 01:38:29,954
- Listen, Tsvika.
- No, Micki, you listen!

938
01:38:30,071 --> 01:38:32,620
- Your wife is here. She's hysterical.
- What?

939
01:38:32,740 --> 01:38:34,913
Is it Micki?
Give me the phone.

940
01:38:35,034 --> 01:38:37,503
- Micki, where is she?
- Where's who?

941
01:38:37,620 --> 01:38:40,214
Your daughter! She's not
answering her cellphone...

942
01:38:40,331 --> 01:38:43,380
- ...and you're not answering yours.
- She's not answering?

943
01:38:43,501 --> 01:38:46,300
Not since you picked her up
from ballet class.

944
01:38:46,421 --> 01:38:48,389
I thought those days
were behind us.

945
01:38:48,506 --> 01:38:50,884
Do you hear me?

946
01:38:57,515 --> 01:38:58,812
Is everything okay?

947
01:40:12,590 --> 01:40:13,716
Dad?

948
01:40:31,067 --> 01:40:33,741
Dad?

949
01:40:33,861 --> 01:40:34,862
Dad.

950
01:40:50,086 --> 01:40:53,431
Don't worry.
I'll do it quickly.

951
01:41:21,284 --> 01:41:24,379
It's a little rusty,
but it'll do the job.

952
01:41:25,663 --> 01:41:27,381
No, no, no!

953
01:41:42,513 --> 01:41:45,608
Enough, son.
That's enough.

954
01:41:48,853 --> 01:41:51,652
- Stop right there.
- What have you done?

955
01:41:52,773 --> 01:41:54,616
You're insane!

956
01:41:56,944 --> 01:41:59,038
I don't think that will help.

957
01:41:59,155 --> 01:42:02,329
He mustn't die! Get me
something to stop the bleeding!

958
01:42:02,450 --> 01:42:05,750
Gidi, I suggest you run quickly,
before the police get here.

959
01:42:05,870 --> 01:42:07,338
Are you people listening to me?

960
01:42:09,248 --> 01:42:12,377
Where did you hide my daughter?

961
01:42:14,045 --> 01:42:15,547
Your daughter?

962
01:42:16,756 --> 01:42:18,258
Please, tell me where she is.

963
01:42:19,383 --> 01:42:20,976
What did you do with her?

964
01:42:26,140 --> 01:42:27,483
What do we do?

965
01:42:37,652 --> 01:42:39,074
Get a piece of paper!

966
01:42:39,195 --> 01:42:40,913
Some paper and a pen.

967
01:42:41,030 --> 01:42:43,658
Gidi, bring something.

968
01:44:35,911 --> 01:44:37,734
Hello.

969
01:44:37,855 --> 01:44:39,323
- Tsvika.
- Yes?

970
01:44:39,440 --> 01:44:41,568
- We're done here.
- Did you find anything?

971
01:44:41,692 --> 01:44:43,365
No, we didn't find anything.

972
01:44:43,486 --> 01:44:46,035
- Wrap it up, then.
- Yes, I'm leaving.

